(189, 4, 47, 1, 'Hymenocallis Caribaea', 'Hymenocallis-Caribaea', 'Hydrangeas-Skyblue.jpg', 'Hydrangeas-Skyblue.jpg', 'Hydrangeas-Skyblue.jpg', 'Hydrangea_arborescens-1.jpg,Hydrangea_EndlessSummer.jpg,Hydrangea_LemonZest.jpg,Hydrangea_macrophylla-3.jpg,Hydrangea_paniculata-2.jpg,Hydrangeas-Paniculata.jpg,Hydrangeas-Skyblue.jpg,Hydrangeas-White.jpg', '<p><strong><br />Hymenocallis caribaea</strong>, also called Spider Lily, Filmy Lily or Sacred Lily of Incas. The flower look like daffodils except for the delicate spider-like petals.ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â  Its from West Indies .InBangkok, you can see this flower on the street, they are on the island in the middle of the road at Sukhumvit road. Hydrangeas grow best in moist, well-drained soil. Most hydrangeas benefit from some shade, especially in hot climates. Bigleaf, oakleaf and smooth hydrangeas will usually perform well on the north side of a house or planted at the edge of a woodland.</p>', 'HC005', 400, '2012-05-14 01:16:09', 5, NULL, '0', '1', '', '', ''),
