(192, 4, 48, 1, 'Snowdrop Flower', 'Snowdrop-Flower', 'snowdrop-flower-5.jpg', 'snowdrop-flower-5.jpg', 'snowdrop-flower-5.jpg', 'blue-snowdrop-flower.jpg,snowdrop-3.jpg,snowdrop-4.jpg,snowdrop-flower-1.jpg,snowdrop-flower-2.jpg,snowdrop-flower-5.jpg', '<p><strong><br />Snowdrops</strong> are perennial flowering plants native to large parts ofEurope. Found in many woodlands, churchyards, parks and gardens. They like a moist soil with plenty of humus and do not like hot weather, dry positions preferring part shade. TheyÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â  grow well in light shade. They can be easily cultivated in gardens. Snowdrops grow wild in Europe andSouthwest Asia. Different types of colors can be seen in winter season.<br />ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â </p>\r\n<p>Scientific name: <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><em>Galanthus</em></strong></span>ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â  <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><em>nivalis</em></strong></span><br />Rank: Species<br />Common names: Common snowdrop<br />ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™Ãƒâ€ Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ã‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â </p>', 'SD003', 245, '2012-05-15 07:27:17', 3, '186,404', '0', '1', '', '', ''),
